=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 17, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104zvk1665702916825.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zvk1665702916825.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zvk1665702916825.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"zvk1665702916825\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Construct the name of the overflow table.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zvk1665702916825__section_v12_rww_fwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d747787e50\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zvk1665702916825__p_d130391e1_d130392e1_d130393e1\">Parse the table name to determine the position of the\n        ‘O’ indicating an overflow table. The purpose of the <code class=\"ph codeph\">Name</code> table request\n        is:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"zvk1665702916825__ul_pws_sww_fwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zvk1665702916825__li_d46775e1_d46776e1_d46777e1\">When <code class=\"ph codeph\">uinfo-&gt;tabname</code> is set to 2\n          in the <code class=\"ph codeph\">Info</code> request, this request is used to determine the position of\n          the ‘O’ indicating an overflow table. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zvk1665702916825__li_d46778e1_d46779e1_d46780e1\">To change the table name.</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zvk1665702916825__p_d130394e1_d130395e1_d130396e1\">If an occurrence of an entity containing\n        variable-length fields grows to more than 8192 bytes, Uniface creates overflow segments that\n        are stored in overflow tables. The overflow table or file has the same name as the ‘main’\n        entity, preceded by an initial ‘O’. The syntax of the table names can be too complex to let\n        Uniface place this ‘O’. An example of this is when database, catalogs, database schema names\n        and separators for these items are included in the entity name. In this case, the Name table\n        request can be used to let the connector place the ‘O’.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zvk1665702916825__p_d130397e1_d130398e1_d130399e1\">Uniface will only issue this request to the DBMS\n        connector when <code class=\"ph codeph\">uinfo-&gt;tabname</code> is set to 2 in the <code class=\"ph codeph\">Info</code>\n        request.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zvk1665702916825__section_eqv_gpx_bcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d747787e89\">From Uniface</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"zvk1665702916825__table_d15572e1_d15573e1_d15574e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Information Available from Uniface</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"zvk1665702916825__table_d15572e1_d15573e1_d15574e1__entry__1\">Data Structure-&gt;Element</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"zvk1665702916825__table_d15572e1_d15573e1_d15574e1__entry__2\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zvk1665702916825__table_d15572e1_d15573e1_d15574e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;umisc</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zvk1665702916825__table_d15572e1_d15573e1_d15574e1__entry__2\">Pointer to the table name.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zvk1665702916825__section_vck_hpx_bcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d747787e136\">To Uniface</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"zvk1665702916825__table_d15575e1_d15576e1_d15577e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Information Supplied to Uniface</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"zvk1665702916825__table_d15575e1_d15576e1_d15577e1__entry__1\">Data Structure-&gt;Element</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"zvk1665702916825__table_d15575e1_d15576e1_d15577e1__entry__2\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zvk1665702916825__table_d15575e1_d15576e1_d15577e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;iobuf</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zvk1665702916825__table_d15575e1_d15576e1_d15577e1__entry__2\">When the DBMS connector wants to return a new table\n                name, it has to provide Uniface with this name in <code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;iobuf</code>.\n                When this is not the case, the DBMS connector has to make sure that\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;iobuf[0]</code> contains ‘/0’. <p class=\"p\">The position where the ‘O’\n                  should be placed in case of an overflow table.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"zvk1665702916825__table_d15578e1_d15579e1_d15580e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 3. </span><span class=\"title\">Connector Request Return Values</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"zvk1665702916825__table_d15578e1_d15579e1_d15580e1__entry__1\">Value</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"zvk1665702916825__table_d15578e1_d15579e1_d15580e1__entry__2\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zvk1665702916825__table_d15578e1_d15579e1_d15580e1__entry__1\">&gt;=0</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zvk1665702916825__table_d15578e1_d15579e1_d15580e1__entry__2\">The position to place the ‘O’ in case of overflow\n                tables.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zvk1665702916825__table_d15578e1_d15579e1_d15580e1__entry__1\">-9</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"zvk1665702916825__table_d15578e1_d15579e1_d15580e1__entry__2\">I/O server logon error.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zvk1665702916825__p_d130406e1_d130407e1_d130408e1\">The connector request return value must be 0. Do not\n        change the value of <code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;udrverr</code>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zvk1665702916825__section_d4f_zww_fwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d747787e242\">Extra information</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zvk1665702916825__p_d130412e1_d130413e1_d130414e1\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">Name</code> table request is provided\n        with a dummy control block. This control block does not describe a table and it does not\n        have an associated connector workspace.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iga1665702915956.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uinfo</a><p>Supplies Uniface with basic information about the DBMS and the connector.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/azl1665702915888.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uctrl</a><p>Exchanges general information between Uniface and the connector, and describes a table.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534642\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534642\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Name table ('N') Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 17, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Construct the name of the overflow table. Description Parse the table name to determine the position of the ‘O’ indicating an overflow table. The purpose of the Name table request is: When uinfo->tabname is set to 2 in the Info request, this request is used to determine the position of the ‘O’ indicating an overflow table. To change the table name. If an occurrence of an entity containing variable-length fields grows to more than 8192 bytes, Uniface creates overflow segments that are stored in overflow tables. The overflow table or file has the same name as the ‘main’ entity, preceded by an initial ‘O’. The syntax of the table names can be too complex to let Uniface place this ‘O’. An example of this is when database, catalogs, database schema names and separators for these items are included in the entity name. In this case, the Name table request can be used to let the connector place the ‘O’. Uniface will only issue this request to the DBMS connector when uinfo->tabname is set to 2 in the Info request. From Uniface Table 1. Information Available from Uniface Data Structure->Element Description uctrl->umisc Pointer to the table name. To Uniface Table 2. Information Supplied to Uniface Data Structure->Element Description uctrl->iobuf When the DBMS connector wants to return a new table name, it has to provide Uniface with this name in uctrl->iobuf . When this is not the case, the DBMS connector has to make sure that uctrl->iobuf[0] contains ‘/0’. The position where the ‘O’ should be placed in case of an overflow table. Table 3. Connector Request Return Values Value Description >=0 The position to place the ‘O’ in case of overflow tables. -9 I/O server logon error. The connector request return value must be 0. Do not change the value of uctrl->udrverr . Extra information The Name table request is provided with a dummy control block. This control block does not describe a table and it does not have an associated connector workspace. Related Links uinfo Supplies Uniface with basic information about the DBMS and the connector. uctrl Exchanges general information between Uniface and the connector, and describes a table. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}